parameters.name: Body
parameters.description: The OpenAPI definition. Supported only for HTTP APIs.

nested_items.name: ApiEndpoint
nested_items.description: The URI of the API, of the form {api-id}.execute-api.{region}.amazonaws.com. The stage name is typically appended to this URI to form a complete path to a deployed API stage.

nested_items.name: ApiGatewayManaged
nested_items.description: Specifies whether an API is managed by API Gateway. You can't update or delete a managed API by using API Gateway. A managed API can be deleted only through the tooling or service that created it.

nested_items.name: ApiId
nested_items.description: The API ID.

nested_items.name: ApiKeySelectionExpression
nested_items.description: An API key selection expression. Supported only for WebSocket APIs. See API Key Selection Expressions.

nested_items.name: CorsConfiguration
nested_items.description: A CORS configuration. Supported only for HTTP APIs.

nested_items.name: AllowCredentials
nested_items.description: Specifies whether credentials are included in the CORS request. Supported only for HTTP APIs.

nested_items.name: AllowHeaders
nested_items.description: Represents a collection of allowed headers. Supported only for HTTP APIs.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: AllowMethods
nested_items.description: Represents a collection of allowed HTTP methods. Supported only for HTTP APIs.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: AllowOrigins
nested_items.description: Represents a collection of allowed origins. Supported only for HTTP APIs.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: ExposeHeaders
nested_items.description: Represents a collection of exposed headers. Supported only for HTTP APIs.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: MaxAge
nested_items.description: The number of seconds that the browser should cache preflight request results. Supported only for HTTP APIs.

nested_items.name: CreatedDate
nested_items.description: The timestamp when the API was created.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: The description of the API.

nested_items.name: DisableSchemaValidation
nested_items.description: Avoid validating models when creating a deployment. Supported only for WebSocket APIs.

nested_items.name: DisableExecuteApiEndpoint
nested_items.description: Specifies whether clients can invoke your API by using the default execute-api endpoint. By default, clients can invoke your API with the default https://{api_id}.execute-api.{region}.amazonaws.com endpoint. To require that clients use a custom domain name to invoke your API, disable the default endpoint.

nested_items.name: ImportInfo
nested_items.description: The validation information during API import. This may include particular properties of your OpenAPI definition which are ignored during import. Supported only for HTTP APIs.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: IpAddressType
nested_items.description: The IP address types that can invoke the API.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the API.

nested_items.name: ProtocolType
nested_items.description: The API protocol.

nested_items.name: RouteSelectionExpression
nested_items.description: The route selection expression for the API. For HTTP APIs, the routeSelectionExpression must be ${request.method} ${request.path}. If not provided, this will be the default for HTTP APIs. This property is required for WebSocket APIs.
(string) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Version
nested_items.description: A version identifier for the API.

nested_items.name: Warnings
nested_items.description: The warning messages reported when failonwarnings is turned on during API import.
(string) ---
